description:
How I made money as a part-time content creator:

- paid to post content on a new app 
- sponsored posts
- affiliate links
- paid article

Mar: $0 - just starting out, i received a few gifted and paid offers up to $150. I was just focused on learning + growing

Apr: $0 - started getting offers up to $400! said no to all of them, still just trying to grow

May: $55 (affiliate links lol) - average deal size grew to $600. I told myself anything less than $1000 wasn’t worth the hassle…

Jun: $1165 - OK so I went back on my goal of $1000 per post. I took a few smaller deals but i was excited for this milestone 🥳!!! 

Jul: $2253 - still learning to pitch, negotiate, and know my worth but SOO grateful for where I’m at 🥹

My goals for the next few months:
- get into UGC 😫 I know I keep saying this but omg I promise soon
- start doing outreach… 0 luck on apps so far and I haven’t sent out any emails/DMs🥶

*NO CREATOR FUND BC IM IN CANADA 🥲*

#contentcreator #monetize #sidehustle #parttimejob #paytransparency #ugc

description:
👇 I was paid $75,000 when I started my job. Inflation adjusted, that amount is worth ~$80,000 almost exactly 2 years later. 

I got a 3.8% performance-based raise last year and then 4% this year, bringing me to my present day salary of… $80,700. So essentially a 1% raise over the course of 2 years. LOL!!! 😠😡🤬 

*Last year, the average rate of inflation was 4.1% in the US and 3.9% in Canada. The year before that was like 8% lol. 

#antiwork #corporatelife #worklife #genzpersonalfinance #inflation
